  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Next Steps in AFD&apos;s Development for International Work  (UK)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is designed to assist the development of a small NGO set up by immigrants from Congo-Brazzaville. The agency began by providing supplementary schooling to young Congolese, and has extended this service to other immigrant groups in East London. In addition to these activities it now supports education projects in five regions of Congo, recently funded through the CGI Education programme, but does all this with only one part-time co-ordinator based in London, and a Programme Manager in Congo. AFD is therefore facing challenges relating to sourcing funding, project management, monitoring and evaluation, and advocacy. It has a committed Board of trustees in the UK but they lack appropriate skills and knowledge as well as experience in international development work. This proposal therefore aims to develop the skills of the agency&apos;s trustees, staff and volunteers through a series of tailor-made training sessions, supported by mentoring and peer learning visits to similar organisations in the UK.</narrative>
  </description>
